{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781682983,"nonce":"LP7n/RQpJGaLQBEp/pYeW5ix/8I=","title":"Aggregation pipeline: COUNT/SUM/AVG/MIN/MAX, GROUP BY, HAVING, DISTINCT","message":"The select builder has no aggregation support at all. There is no COUNT/SUM/AVG/MIN/MAX, no GROUP BY, no HAVING, and no DISTINCT. A query as common as \"count posts per user\" cannot be expressed today.\n\nThe select chain in `crates/squealy/src/query.rs` is: from -\u003e where_ -\u003e join/left_join -\u003e on -\u003e order_by -\u003e limit/offset -\u003e select, and stops there.\n\nScope:\n- Aggregate expression constructors over a column/expr (count, sum, avg, min, max), including COUNT(*).\n- group_by(|row| ...) producing a grouped query whose projection is restricted to grouping keys + aggregates.\n- having(|row| ...) predicate over the grouped projection.\n- distinct() on the select (and ideally DISTINCT ON for the pg backend).\n- Result decoding: SUM/AVG nullability and widening (e.g. SUM(i32) -\u003e i64/numeric) must be modelled in the value-type mapping.\n\nThis threads through the type-level AST in expr.rs and the renderers in crates/squealy/src/render.rs plus each backend sql.rs. Largest single functional gap in the query builder.","files":null}]}